<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE43FF88FF32FB115D3AF9AE" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE43FF88FF32FB115864FA8E" blockId="3.[174,1233,1246,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Palaearctic: Europe: widely distributed from Scandinavia to 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FB8DFB1058D8FB4F" box="[1116,1182,1246,1272]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Spain</collectingCountry>
and the British Isles to Siberia. North Africa. Asia: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FD35FB305F7DFAAF" box="[740,827,1278,1304]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FC98FB305F9DFAAF" box="[841,987,1278,1304]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FC38FB30581DFAAF" box="[1001,1115,1278,1304]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FB56FB31588BFAAE" box="[1159,1229,1279,1305]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Japan</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FF7FFAD15CA5FA8E" box="[174,227,1311,1337]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FF3CFAD15DAAFA8E" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[237,492,1310,1337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="45 - 58" refId="ref6384" refString="Knutson, L. V., Berg, C. O. 1963. Biology and immature stages of a snail-killing fly, Hydromya dorsalis (Fabricius) (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Proceedings of Royal Entomological Society of London. Ser. A: Genetic Entomology, 38 (4 - 6), 45 - 58." type="journal article" year="1963">Knutson, Berg (1963)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FE26FAD05858FA8E" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." box="[503,1054,1310,1337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade Namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE43FF88FF32FAF05D3AF9AE" blockId="3.[174,1233,1246,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
Biology. Larvae predate mainly the aquatic gastropods living on wet edge of various lentic freshwater habitats, predominantly 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE43FF88FD7AFA905F7CFACF" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[683,826,1374,1400]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Lymnaeidae</taxonomicName>
species and also attack their egg masses with or without embryos or not (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FD4DFAB05FD3FA2F" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[668,917,1406,1433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="45 - 58" refId="ref6384" refString="Knutson, L. V., Berg, C. O. 1963. Biology and immature stages of a snail-killing fly, Hydromya dorsalis (Fabricius) (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Proceedings of Royal Entomological Society of London. Ser. A: Genetic Entomology, 38 (4 - 6), 45 - 58." type="journal article" year="1963">Knutson, Berg, 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FC72FAB0581BFA2E" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[931,1117,1406,1433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FBA3FAB05CBCFA0E" author="Vaillant, F." pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 258" refId="ref7318" refString="Vaillant, F. 1956. Recherches sur la faune madicole (hygropetrique, s. 1.) de France, de Corse et d'Afrique du Nord. Memoire du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle. Ser. A. Zoologie, 11, 1 - 258." type="journal article" year="1956">Vaillant (1956)</bibRefCitation>
found larvae in many madicole microhabitat in 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE43FF88FCF7FA515F3FFA0E" box="[806,889,1439,1465]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">France</collectingCountry>
. All the immature stages have been described by 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FE59FA715ECFFA6E" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[392,649,1470,1497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="45 - 58" refId="ref6384" refString="Knutson, L. V., Berg, C. O. 1963. Biology and immature stages of a snail-killing fly, Hydromya dorsalis (Fabricius) (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Proceedings of Royal Entomological Society of London. Ser. A: Genetic Entomology, 38 (4 - 6), 45 - 58." type="journal article" year="1963">Knutson, Berg (1963)</bibRefCitation>
. The puparia are formed outside of the snail host, on wet edge of the larval habitat (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FD96FA105F04FA4E" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[583,834,1502,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="45 - 58" refId="ref6384" refString="Knutson, L. V., Berg, C. O. 1963. Biology and immature stages of a snail-killing fly, Hydromya dorsalis (Fabricius) (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Proceedings of Royal Entomological Society of London. Ser. A: Genetic Entomology, 38 (4 - 6), 45 - 58." type="journal article" year="1963">Knutson, Berg, 1963</bibRefCitation>
). This species seems multivoltine (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE43FF88FF67FA305D36F9AE" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[182,368,1534,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
